#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Crip-phase1-bundle.md:1
msgid "RIP Phase 1 Bundle"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Crip-phase1-bundle.md:3
msgid ""
"The **RIP Phase 1 Bundle** is the first government process bundle shipped "
"with the Linked Data Explorer for the Province of Flevoland. It automates "
"the project definition and preliminary design preparation phases of the "
"Regular Infrastructure Projects (RIP) workflow, from intake through to "
"approved preliminary design principles."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Crip-phase1-bundle.md:5
msgid ""
"The bundle lives at `examples/organizations/flevoland/rip-phase1/` alongside "
"the existing HR onboarding bundle, and is deployed to Operaton in a single "
"multipart request via the BPMN Modeler's Deploy modal."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Crip-phase1-bundle.md:14
msgid "Process flow"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Crip-phase1-bundle.md:16
msgid ""
"The process has seventeen steps across two phases and two approval gateways."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Crip-phase1-bundle.md:18
msgid "**Phase 1 — Project definition**"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Crip-phase1-bundle.md:20
msgid ""
"The process starts with an intake form where the project contributor "
"registers the project. A BusinessRuleTask evaluates the "
"`RipProjectTypeAssignment` DMN to assign `candidateGroups` and "
"`assignedRoles` based on `projectType` and `department`. A ServiceTask then "
"creates the project workspace in eDOCS via the external task worker. After "
"the intake meeting is organised and held, the contributor completes the "
"intake report. A second ServiceTask uploads the report to eDOCS. A "
"designated reviewer then approves or rejects the report — rejection loops "
"back to the intake report step."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Crip-phase1-bundle.md:22
msgid "**Phase 2 — Preliminary design preparation**"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Crip-phase1-bundle.md:24
msgid ""
"Once the intake report is approved, the PSU (project start-up meeting) is "
"organised and executed. Outcomes are recorded in the PSU execution form and "
"turned into a PSU report document, which is saved to eDOCS. The contributor "
"then prepares the risk file in Relatics and records the reference number. "
"Finally, the preliminary design principles document is authored, saved to "
"eDOCS, and submitted for approval. Rejection loops back to the preliminary "
"design principles step."
msgstr ""

